# Liquid Glass Key Rules

## Principles
- Theme: Transparency, glass texture, fluidity for futuristic aesthetics.
- Goals: Content visibility; WCAG AA compliance (contrast ≥4.5:1); light/dark modes; fallbacks for low-performance (disable backdrop-filter, use opacity 0.9).
- Integration: CSS variables; PandaCSS tokens.

## Visual Elements

### Transparency & Material
- Panels: Opacity 60-80%; Gaussian blur 20-30px.
- Adjust opacity dynamically for contrast over backgrounds.
- Base color: White/black + 10-20% opacity.
- Fallback: Solid rgba(255,255,255,0.9) if no backdrop-filter.

### Layers & Depth
- Cards: Soft shadows 10-20% opacity, blur 30-50px.
- Order: Background → Blurred glass → Content → Floating controls.
- Focus: Glow borders rgba(255,255,255,0.5).

### Dynamic Effects
- Interactions: 0.2-0.4s duration, cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1) easing.
- Fluidity: Blur/refraction shifts on scroll/hover.
- Fallback: No animations on low-perf.

### Rounded Corners & Borders
- Radii: 12-20px uniform.
- Borders: 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.18).

## Colors & Fonts
- Colors: Soft gradients (blue-purple, cyan-green, warm orange); adapt light/dark.
- Backgrounds: Auto-system theme.
- Fonts: SF Pro Display (headings), SF Pro Text (body); -apple-system fallback.
- Contrast: ≥4.5:1; validate WCAG AA.

